<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Newswall</title>
    <style>
        li {
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Newswall</h1>
    <p>This is little node.js website to render newspapers for <a href="https://www.visionect.com/shop/place-play-32/ref/pathikrit/" target="_blank">e-ink displays</a> (original idea by <a href="https://onezero.medium.com/the-morning-paper-revisited-35b407822494" target="_blank">Max Braun</a>):</p>
    <ul>
        <li><a href="/latest">/latest</a>: Cycles through grayscaled front pages of newspapers on each refresh. You should point your e-ink device to this link.</li>
        <li>/latest/XXX: Only fetches a particular newspaper. This server is configured to support the following:</li>
            <ol>
                <% papers.forEach((paper) => {%>
                    <li><a href="/latest/<%= paper.key %>">/latest/<%= paper.key %></a>: <%= paper.name %></li>
                <% }) %>
            </ol>
        <li><a href="/archive">/archive</a>: Archive of newspapers courtesy of the <a href="https://www.freedomforum.org/todaysfrontpages/" target="_blank">The Freedom Forum</a></li>
    </ul>
    <p>Checkout the <a href="https://github.com/pathikrit/newswall" target="_blank">github project</a> for more details.</p>
</body>
</html>